HEADWORD: Wattled
<hw>Wat"tled</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Furnished with
wattles, or pendent fleshy processes at the chin or throat.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>wattled</qex> cocks strut to and fro.</q>
<rj><qau>Longfellow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wattless</ent>⟦br⟧
